(116, 1, '2016-02-26 00:13:16', '2016-02-26 00:13:16', '"The Fashionista DJ" | As the Corporate Fashion Director for Nordstrom, Heather crafted sophisticated soundtracks for designer fashion shows across the country. Now a DJ in Washington DC and New York, Heather has been responsible for the musical backdrop to high profile events in locales from the Air &amp; Space Museum in DC to Grand Central Station in NY. Her sets proudly span genres &amp; cultures, with a strong nod to the sun drenched sounds of the Mediteranean. Origionally discovering dance music culture via classic clubs, such as the Sound Factory and The Shelter in NY, and Tracks in DC, she has a deep rooted love for house music. She can currently be found in several venues in DC for monthly appearances as well as a weekly Tuesday event devoted to the best sounds of Ibiza past and present.\r\n\r\n<iframe width="100%" height="180" src="https://www.mixcloud.com/widget/iframe/?embed_type=widget_standard&amp;embed_uuid=a7bb24fb-f4bc-46b4-8c70-e607fa50441d&amp;feed=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mixcloud.com%2Fdjheatherfemia%2Flive-mix-w%2F&amp;hide_cover=1&amp;hide_tracklist=1&amp;replace=0" frameborder="0"></iframe>\r\n<div style="clear: both; height: 3px; width: 652px;"></div>\r\n', 'HEATHER FEMIA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'heather-femia', '', '', '2016-02-26 00:15:38', '2016-02-26 00:15:38', '', 0, 'http://localhost/skylite-wp/?p=116', 0, 'post', '', 0),
